They have multiple exterior seating options with front patio and street side table service with cabana. Friendly and considerate staff coupled with good food and Prosecco. It was also nice to dine indoors during these challenging times (not to mention cold weather).

Definitely one of my favorite restaurants in NYC for the quality, price, and experience. Much better than Little Italy in Manhattan. Intimate setting with delicious homemade pasta and good quality wine. Favorites on the menu: burrata, nudi pasta, lemon marscapone cake.  I absolutely love dining here and go here every time I go to the Bronx Botanical Gardens. At least 4 times per year!

italian food and the feeling at this place is excellent. The service here is above par.

My boyfriend and I were excited to try San Gennaro. The reviews were all positive. We made a reservation but upon arriving the restaurant was pretty empty so this was likely not needed. We were seated outside in a nice cozy table on the patio. From the moment we were seated our waiter was obnoxious in asking for our order. We didn't have 2 minutes to look at the wine list when he is asking us for entrée. We ended up ordering a bottle of wine and appetizer but that did not deter him from coming over literally every 2-3 mins to ask for our order. While I totally ubderstand tables are limited during this tough time the place was empty. I could only imagine how rushed someone would feel on a Friday or Saturday evening. The food was was decent but with all the offerings along Arthur Avenue we probably will not be back.

Very small restaurant (as are most places in this neighborhood). People very friendly.  Some dishes were excellent and some not.  Two of us had veal and those were excellent.  My wife had eggplant Parmesan and that was a very small portion (especially for the price) but it tasted just ok.  My dish was Cavilaletti Peace d'mare was was expensive but not good at all.  Very stingy on the seafood - 2 shrimp, few clams (several empty shells) small calamari and a few mussels.  Taste was not great.  Maybe a place where you might need to know what to order.

Cannot speak to the food as we were not served. Made and modified reservations on OpenTable as we had traveled 20+ miles for Bronx Zoo Holiday lights. Should have been a seemless pre holiday family evening out in my elderly fathers old neighborhood. Upon arrival Genaro was visibly annoyed commenting NOT Welcome... but eye rolling, you must be from Open Table...indicated very loudly, embarrassing us in front of whole (tiny, loud restaurant) that he had a 26 person party coming and we’d have to be out in 35 mins..huh?...Plus a bizarre (especially inappropriate considering the situation) commentary about how busy and popular his restaurant is..he called my dad rude when he asked him to stop shouting at us, took no responsibility for the reservation snafu and made us so uncomfortable we packed up our 3 young children and older parents out into the cold, wet late evening to find another restaurant...there’s tons of great restaurants over there(Antonio’s down street was warm, welcoming, and delicious) if you’re unkind, unwelcoming, and egotistical? We’ll Definitely eat elsewhere!

Nice , fine dining Italian restaurant right in the heart of Auther Ave, ie Little Italy in the Bronx.  The pasta and sauce are great. The deserts are good too. Living in the five boroughs all my life and I must say the moment I walked into this place I was transported to Italy. The ambiance was so welcoming. There was an accessible ramp on for anyone in need. The service was prompt and attentive to all of our needs even with small children. The olive oil that accompanied the fresh bread so refreshing. Each course was so fresh. I highly recommend coming here if you are looking for an authentic Italian meal in the city I've yet to find any other place in the city that comes close.

I walked in at 5PM just as they were opening and asked if they had gluten free options. The owner said of course, we make our own GF pasta. He proceeded to tell me about their homemade GF ravioli, rigatoni and pappardelle. I hugged him right then and there. The Grilled Sardines over arugula with a very light lemon dressing (might have been just lemon juice) was an amazing appetizer. My wife had the special of the day, a seafood lasagna with a bechamel. She loved it. For main course I had their homemade GF Pappardelle with a Ragu. Best GF pasta I ever ate. They sell frozen packages of it to take home so I bought three different ones. My new favorite restaurant on Arthur Avenue. I cannot wait to go back.

Everything was amazing. I will definitely return.  P.S. it was my brother's birthday and he tried to pass on dessert, so the staff made him get a dessert.. free of charge and he loved it.

Great place, friendly and professional staff. Owner and chef come out to greet guests, especially when there is a certain dish you especially enjoy. The food is so delicious and they are usually open longer than any of the restaurants in the area.  I happened to go with a friend on a Wednesday night and this was the only place that was open.  They never rushed us with our meal and the chef and owner regaled us with stories.  It has not been my first visit and they have never disappointed.  Try this place.  It may be smaller in size than many of the competitors, but they are big on taste and service.  By the way, the owner was on the foodnetwork show Throwdown with Bobby Flay and won.

Staff was wonderful. My wife and I were on our last day of a long, Labor Day weekend, and wanted to see this "little Italy", as it was recommended to us. This was one of the only places open at the time (it was Labor Day, and early), and we decided to eat our last NYC meal here. Everything was fantastic, albeit a teeny bit pricey (might be right on par for NYC meal prices, but just not what I am used to). Nonetheless, would definitely recommend.

One of the only truly authentic Italian restaurants in all of the Bronx as well as New York State. The waiters were absolutely amazing and gave Profesional service. The setting is peaceful, and great for family dinner,  large groups or a romantic night out. The appetizers are tasty with a lovely presentation. The main course will be your favorite part.  Whether it's a 30 ounce steak or chicken Parmesan the chef who you can meet personally cooks everything with love and care.  Also please do not skip on the cheesecake and other delicious baked goods because it will help close out the amazing experience with authentic Italian coffee. If you have a large group please make a reservation so they can give you the best service possible.
